    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Joints formed by joining the ends of boards together, end-to-end. In construction, given that heading joints must be supported by joists or bearers, the joints often appear in a straight line.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
